description:
The Validator class is the base class for all Flex validators. This class implements the ability for a validator to make a field required, which means that the user must enter a value in the field or the validation fails.   <p>The Validator class defines the following tag attributes, which all of its subclasses inherit:</p>  <pre>
 &lt;mx:Validator
 enabled=&quot;true|false&quot;
 listener=&quot;<i>Value of the source property</i>&quot;
 property=&quot;<i>No default</i>&quot;
 required=&quot;true|false&quot;
 requiredFieldError=&quot;This field is required.&quot;
 source=&quot;<i>No default</i>&quot;
 trigger=&quot;<i>Value of the source property</i>&quot;
 triggerEvent=&quot;valueCommit&quot;
 /&gt;
 </pre>
